---------------------------------------------------------------
PRACTICAL 4(c): Automate Any Process Using Web Recording
----------------------------------------------------------------

AIM:
To use UiPath Web Recording to automate a web-based task in
Google Chrome — specifically, searching for a term on Google.

THEORY:
Web Recording wraps all recorded actions inside an "Open Browser"
or "Attach Browser" container. It is optimized for web automation
and generates reliable selectors for web elements.

PRE-REQUISITES:
- Google Chrome browser.
- UiPath Chrome Extension installed.
  (Go to UiPath Studio: Tools > UiPath Extensions > Chrome > Install)

STEPS:

Step 1: Create a New Project
  - Open UiPath Studio.
  - Click "New Project" > "Process".
  - Name it: web_recording_demo
  - Click "Create".

Step 2: Open Google Chrome
  - Open Chrome and go to: https://www.google.com

Step 3: Start Web Recording
  - In UiPath Studio, click "Recording" > "Web".
  - The Web Recording toolbar appears.

Step 4: Indicate the Browser
  - Click "Indicate Browser" or "Open Browser" in the toolbar.
  - Click anywhere on the Chrome window.
  - An "Open Browser" or "Attach Browser" container is created.

Step 5: Record Clicking the Search Box
  - In the Recording toolbar, click "Type".
  - Click on Google's search input box.
  - In the dialog that appears, type: UiPath RPA Tutorial
  - Click OK.

Step 6: Record Pressing Enter
  - Click "Type" in the Recording toolbar.
  - Click the search box again.
  - In the dialog, leave text blank and set: [k(enter)]
  - OR use "Send Hotkey" > Enter.

Step 7: Stop Recording
  - Press Escape or click "Save & Exit".
  - UiPath generates the workflow.

Step 8: Run
  - Press F5.
  - Chrome opens, types the search term, presses Enter.
  - Google shows search results for "UiPath RPA Tutorial".

EXPECTED OUTPUT:
  Google Chrome displays search results for "UiPath RPA Tutorial".

